50|$|Operation Phantom Linebacker was a {{coalition}} military <b>operation</b> <b>in</b> <b>Iraq</b> designed to interdict anti-government fighters from entering Iraq from Syria. The U.S. 3rd Brigade and the 2nd Infantry Division (United States) conducted the operation with the Iraqi National Guard, Iraqi Border Police, and other Multinational Forces. The U.S. III Corps uses ‘Phantom’ as its nickname. Launched in early August 2004.|$|R
